I"ß<p>This short tutorial is made to show you how to create a <strong>fade in</strong> / <strong>fade out</strong> effect for a form. Since basic Windows Forms doesnâ€™t provide such an option, it must be done manually.</p>

<p><em>Note: weâ€™ll use timers instead of general repetitive structures to avoid thread blocking</em></p>

<h2 id="fade-in-effect">Fade in Effect</h2>

<p>To do this, all we have to do is to set the Formâ€™s <strong>Opacity</strong> to <strong>0</strong>. Then, using a <strong>Timer</strong> weâ€™ll slowly increase opacity. All this code should go in a event handler that is executed when the form loads.</p>

<p>As an example:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-csharp" data-lang="csharp"><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
